Q1

  • admission year
  • admission month
  • admission week day
  • admission hour
  • length of hospital stay
  • admission type
  • number of admissions per patient
  • admission location
  • insurance
  • language
  • religion
  • martial status
  • ethnicity

  • admission year
#not unique data
admissions %>%
  mutate(adm_year = year(ADMITTIME)) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = adm_year))

-admission month

#not unique data
admissions %>%
  mutate(adm_month = month(ADMITTIME, label = TRUE)) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = adm_month)) +
  labs(x = "Admission month")

-admission week day

#not unique data
admissions %>%
  mutate(adm_weekday = wday(ADMITTIME, label = TRUE)) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = adm_weekday)) +
  labs(x = "Admission week day")

-admission hour

#not unique data
admissions %>%
  mutate(adm_hour = hour(ADMITTIME)) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = adm_hour)) +
  labs(x = "Admission hour")

-admission minute

admissions %>%
  mutate(adm_min = minute(ADMITTIME)) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_freqpoly(mapping = aes(x = adm_min)) +
  labs(x = "Admission minute")
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

-length of hospital stay

#not unique data
admissions %>%
  mutate(lenstay = as.numeric(as.duration(DISCHTIME - ADMITTIME) / 86400)) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_histogram(mapping = aes(x = lenstay),bins = 100) +
  labs(x = "Length of hospital stay in (days)")

  • admission type
#unique data
admissionsUNIQ<-distinct(admissions,SUBJECT_ID,.keep_all = TRUE)
ggplot(data = admissionsUNIQ) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = ADMISSION_TYPE))

  • number of admissions per patient
admissionsnum <- admissions %>% 
  group_by(SUBJECT_ID) %>% 
  summarise(
    count = n())
ggplot(data = admissionsnum) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = count))

  • death
admissionsdie <- admissions %>% 
  filter(is.na(DEATHTIME)==FALSE) %>%
  separate(DEATHTIME,into = c("year", "month","weekday","hour","minute","second")) %>%
  group_by(year) %>% 
  summarise(
    count = n())
ggplot(data = admissionsdie) + 
  geom_point(mapping=aes(x=year,y=count))

Note it is possible that one patient (uniquely identified by the SUBJECT_ID) is admitted into hospital multiple times. When summarizing some demographic information, it makes sense to summarize based on only unique patients.

Q3

Q4

CHARTEVENTS.csv (https://mimic.physionet.org/mimictables/chartevents/) contains all the charted data available for a patient. During their ICU stay, the primary repository of a patients information is their electronic chart. The ITEMID variable indicates a single measurement type in the database. The VALUE variable is the value measured for ITEMID.

D_ITEMS.csv (https://mimic.physionet.org/mimictables/d_items/) is the dictionary for the ITEMID in CHARTEVENTS.csv. Find potential values of ITEMID that correspond to systolic blood pressure, i.e., LABEL contains the string systolic.

Compile a tibble that contains the first ICU stay of unique patients, with the patients demographic information, the first systolic blood pressure measurement during ICU stay, and whether the patient died within 30 days of hospitcal admission.
